        "position": "I understand Mom wants 4 nights in Moganshan/Anji area, but as the driver and budget controller, I need to balance travel fatigue with our ¥15,000 total budget. Four nights of minsu accommodation plus cultural activities could strain our budget significantly. I propose a hybrid solution: 3 nights total with one camping night (free accommodation, saves ¥400-600) and two nights in a family-friendly minsu. This allows Mom's cultural experiences while maintaining budget control and giving our kid the camping adventure he'd love learning from."
